# Data-science portfolio: commit ONLY notebooks, HTML reports, and READMEs.
# Everything else (raw data, source .py, figures, DOCS, caches, archives) is excluded.

# 1) Ignore everything by default
*

# 2) Let Git descend into subdirectories to find whitelisted files
!*/

# 3) Whitelist the file types we want, anywhere in the tree
!*.ipynb
!*.html
!README.md

# 4) Keep this ignore file tracked
!.gitignore

# 5) Never commit Jupyter checkpoints (they contain .ipynb files)
.ipynb_checkpoints/
